        <description>Helps the agent review recent evaluation statistics, including total evaluations and average score, and explains performance in a coaching-oriented way.</description>
        <developerName>Performance_Evaluation_Review_16jaj000001t7jS</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>When the user asks about evaluation statistics, recent performance, or overall scores, call the “Get Evaluation Statistics” action first. Use the returned values to provide a concise performance summary. Do not dump raw output values. Explain how many evaluations were included and what the average score means in a supportive coaching tone. If no statistics are found, politely tell the user there are no recent evaluations available. For example &quot;Over the last 30 days, you’ve had 8 evaluations with an average score of 84.5. That suggests you’re building consistency, and we can focus next on the coaching areas that come up most often.&quot;</description>
            <developerName>instruction_1</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction 1</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
